OL,3,CShoplifting offences in England and
OL,4,CWales hit a 20-year high
OL,6,FMeghan Elkin, from the ONS, said:
OL,7,F"There has been no change across many
OL,8,Fcrime types in the last year. However,
OL,9,Fwe have seen falls in fraud while
OL,10,Fthere have been increases in computer
OL,11,Fmisuse and some forms of theft, such
OL,12,Fas shoplifting and theft from the
OL,13,Fperson. Notably, shoplifting has
OL,14,Fcontinued to see increases and remains
OL,15,Fat its highest level in 20 years.
